item.title: Eksempelside

item.content:encoded:
Dette er en eksempelside. Den er forskellig fra et indlg, fordi den vil forblive det samme sted og vre en del af dit websteds navigation (i de fleste temaer). De fleste vil lgge ud med en Om-side, der prsenterer dem for potentielle besgende. Ordlyden kunne vre noget i retning af:
Hejsa! Jeg er cykelbud om dagen, prver at blive skuespiller om aftenen og dette er min blog. Jeg bor i Kbenhavn, har en dejlig hund, der hedder King, og jeg kan lide Mojitos. (og at blive overrasket af regnvejr.)
... eller noget i retning af:
XYZ Dingenot fabrikken blev grundlagt i 1971 og har leveret kvalitetsdingenoter til offentligheden lige siden. Beliggende i Andeby, har 2.000 ansatte og bidrager med alverdens seje tiltag i lokalomrdet.
Som ny WordPress bruger, br du g til dit kontrolpanel for at slette denne side og oprette nye sider til dit indhold. God fornjelse!

item.title: Edificio Cion
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Edificio Cion

Built in 2001 and designed by Fernando Menis, The private housing building has 3 floors. A little light yard glazed with tempered glass naturally illuminates and ventilates the interior rooms. The only facade facing the street is solved in a Mediterranean architectural way with mobile concrete panels and phenolic coloured wooden slats with different colors, all versatile and sustainable features. The materials used in the construction are seen coloured concrete, phenolic wood and stone.

item.title: Edificio Olympo
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Edificio Olympo

Edificio Olympo is a skyscraper in the city of Santa Cruz on the Tenerife, Canary Islands, Spain. Completed in 1975, has 19 floors and rises 57 meters. Plaza de la Candelaria 1, near some other skyscrapers, including Torres de Santa Cruz and Rascacielos de la avenida Tres de Mayo. It has an innovative and distinctive look. Main usage: offices, residential and shopping center. Plaza de la Candelaria 1, near some other skyscrapers, including Torres de Santa Cruz and Rascacielos de la avenida Tres de Mayo. It has an innovative and distinctive look. Main usage: offices, residential and shopping center.

item.title: TEA Espacio De Las Artes
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
TEA Espacio De Las Artes

The Tenerife Space of Arts (Tenerife Espacio de las Artes - TEA); is a building of approximately 20,622 square metres that houses the contemporary museum scar Domnguez Institute (Instituto scar Domnguez); the Alejandro Cioranescu Island Library (Biblioteca Insular Alejandro Cioranescu) and the Center for Photography Island of Tenerife (Centro de Fotografa Isla de Tenerife). In addition, the property has a hall, a restaurant, a shop, a public square, and many offices.   This cultural space, promoted by the Council of Tenerife (Cabildo de Tenerife), is located in the center of the city of Santa Cruz de Tenerife, the island of Tenerife (Canary Islands, Spain), on the banks of the Gulley of Santos (Barranco de Santos); between the market of Nuestra Seora de Africa and the Church of the Conception (Iglesia de la Concepcin), and near the Museum of Nature and Man (Museo de la Naturaleza y el Hombre). The building was designed by the Swiss firm of architects Herzog & de Meuron and directed by the Canary architect Virgilio Gutierrez Herreros.

item.title: Presidencia Del Gobierno
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Presidencia Del Gobierno

Building began on the headquarters of the Regional Canarian Government in Santa Cruz de Tenerife in 1993. It was designed by Felipe Artengo Rufino, Fernando Martin Menis and Jose Maria Rodriguez-Pastrana, all architects from Tenerife. The use of volcanic materials, stone, metal and wood have resulted in a beautiful building. In the courtyard, which is accessible to the public, there is a splendid authentic Canarian balcony made of carved wood. This balcony was retrieved from an old stately home on the island and adds a great finishing touch to the building as a whole.

item.title: Auditorio
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Auditorio

Auditorio de Tenerife takes another step forward in the relationship with their publics under the slogan a new conversation. Both communication channel sand forms of dialogue, between a cultural center and their audiences, have multiplied exponentially and this allow us approaches and relationships that we had not deployed until now. New times also generate new insights and for us, as a public space, it is very important to create a common place where we can share our views on the artistic and cultural activity, while listen to everything you want to say to produce a collaborative space of social participation, to improve our citizenship through the social and cultural value that the arts brings to all of us.

item.title: Centro Internacional De Ferias Y Congresos
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Centro Internacional De Ferias Y Congresos

The Tenerife International Centre for Trade Fairs and Congresses, located in the expansion area of Santa Cruz de Tenerife, has become the new image of the capitals southern entrance. Its strategic position combines ease of access and fast motorway communication with Tenerifes two airports, the port and any point on the island. This enormous enclosuredesigned by architect and engineer Santiago Calatrava and commissioned by the Cabildo Insular de Tenerife (Tenerife Island Council)its modern infrastructure and equipment, as well as a wide range of services, make this multi-purpose arena the perfect place for business, cultural, sports and leisure activities. The Trade Fair Centre, which presides over the Avenida de la Constitucin, opposite the leisure complex of Parque Martimo Csar Manrique, completes the economic and social proposal of an area that also houses the Law Courts, Palmetum (Palm Tree Gardens) and the new Auditorium.

Espacio Cultural El Tanque

At the stand at ARCO 2012 (from 15 to 19 February), you can enjoy the installation designed by Fernando Menis including various models made of concrete such as The Tanque itself as well as the Church of the Chumberas among others. The stand is curated by Dulce Xerach, vice president of the Association Amigos del Espacio Cultural El Tanque.

item.title: SKIBET FRDIGGRES
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Kopien af Ladbyskibet bygges lige ved museet p en til formlet anrettet byggeplads. Her blev ogs Gokstadbden bygget. Museets gster er meget velkomne p pladsen. Hver tirsdag, onsdag og torsdag kl. 10-15 er der arbejdsdag for alle de frivillige, og pladsen myldrer af liv. Vi glder os over arbejdet - og ikke mindst til at komme til ss!

item.title: SKIBET SSTTES
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded: Frst en bd, s et skib Fordi opgaven at bygge en sstrk kopi af Ladbyskibet i fuld skala er en kmpe udfordring, prvede bdebyggerne - efter rd fra eksperter fra Vikingeskibsmuseet i Roskilde - frst krfter med et vikingeskibsbyggeprojekt i mindre skala. Efter nje overvejelser blev den mindste af de tre bde, der blev fundet ved Gokstadskibet i Norge i 1880, og som kan dateres til omkring 895, valgt som velegnet til at blive kopieret. Gokstadbden blev frdiggjort i december 2011 og ssat i Kerteminde Fjord i maj 2012. Efterflgende har den om sommeren ligget p svaj i fjorden ud for vikingeskibshjen, mens vinteren tilbringes p land.   Men nu er rekonstruktionen af Ladbyskibet nsten frdig! Det vil sige at skibet snart skal ssttes i Kerteminde Fjord. Dette vil ske d. 16 maj 2016, hvor der udover sstningen vil vre en masse spndende arrangementer i lbet af dagen. S tag familien med ud til Vikingemuseet Ladby og f en unik oplevelse!

item.title: Pabellon Ana Bautista
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Pabellon Ana Bautista

The site where the Rhythmic and Olimpic Gymnastics Sports Complex is located lies in a half-moon shape strip of land, next to Barranco Santos ravine in the Canary Islands, future axis of green architecture in the city of Santa Cruz. Versatile and functional architecture. A light curved roof that rises above the floor in the shape of a wave and falling over the recessed square to let direct access to the upper stands. The structure is solved with ten laminated-wood arches, which leans on five metallic columns before a large linear window, simulating five gymnasts supporting the 40m of light and 16m of height structure.

item.title: Casa MM
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Casa MM

On one hand, the staircase hangs up from the roof by tubes and metal sheet, retrieved from dismantled oil tanks, to which metal made steps are soldered, and covered with concrete using the remains of short steel bars left over from building work. On the other hand, regarding the facade, we experiment with a system of lamellas constructed with galvanized water pipes and wood. The lamellas can be moved in order to control the sunlight and the views. The building, set on a corner, is separated from the near walls by a different sections patio which provides ventilation, natural light and acoustic comfort.

item.title: Casa Hernandez-Frances
item.dc:creator: admin
item.content:encoded:
Casa Hernandez-Frances

The house is solved in net volumes and powerful contrasts seeking more or less rough and hard materials, and play with figures like cracks or crystalline mineralogy abutments. Strong volumes enclosing a comfortable layout and solve the corner gently, skillfully managing the distances to the perimeter. Project started in 1962, completed 1964 Located: Calle enrique wolfson, 4 Encargo Jos B. Hernndez-Francs Oramas
